    IP_ASSETS --> EVENT_SOURCE
    ORG_ASSETS --> EVENT_SOURCE
    PERSON_ASSETS --> EVENT_SOURCE
```

The event processing pipeline operates through an `EventDispatcher` that manages a `HandlerRegistry` of plugins. Each plugin handler has a specific priority and processes different asset types. DNS handlers discover network infrastructure with priorities ranging from 1-8, while API enrichment plugins gather organizational intelligence. The system creates a feedback loop where discovered assets generate new events for further processing.

Sources: [README.md:10-10]()

## Plugin System and Data Sources

Amass uses a plugin-based architecture to integrate with various data sources and discovery techniques:

### DNS Infrastructure and Discovery

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "DNS Infrastructure"
        BASELINE_RESOLVERS["Baseline Trusted Resolvers<br/>Google, Cloudflare, Quad9"]
        PUBLIC_RESOLVERS["Dynamic Public Resolvers<br/>from public-dns.info"]
        RESOLVER_POOL["DNS Resolver Pool<br/>Load Balanced"]
    end
    
    subgraph "DNS Query Engine"
        QUERY_MANAGER["DNS Query Manager"]
        WILDCARD_DETECTOR["Wildcard Detector"]
        TTL_CACHE["TTL-based Cache"]
        QPS_LIMITER["QPS Rate Limiter"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Asset Discovery"
        FQDN_INPUT["Target Domains"]
        IP_DISCOVERY["IP Address Discovery"]
        SUBDOMAIN_ENUM["Subdomain Enumeration"]
        REVERSE_DNS["Reverse DNS Lookups"]
        NETWORK_MAPPING["Network Mapping"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Network Intelligence"
        ASN_INFO["ASN Information"]
        NETBLOCK_DATA["Network Blocks"]
        WHOIS_DATA["WHOIS Records"]
        ORG_ATTRIBUTION["Organization Attribution"]
    end
    
    BASELINE_RESOLVERS --> RESOLVER_POOL
    PUBLIC_RESOLVERS --> RESOLVER_POOL
    
    RESOLVER_POOL --> QUERY_MANAGER
    QUERY_MANAGER --> WILDCARD_DETECTOR
    QUERY_MANAGER --> TTL_CACHE
