This document describes the command-line interface (CLI) of OWASP Amass, which serves as the primary method for users to interact with Amass's capabilities. The CLI provides access to various subdomain enumeration and asset discovery features through subcommands and flags. For information about specific configuration options, see [Configuration](#3).

## Overview of the Command Line Structure

Amass follows a subcommand structure where the main executable (`amass`) routes to different specialized commands. Each subcommand implements its own CLI workflow through dedicated modules.

### Command Line Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    User -->|"executes"| main["main() in cmd/amass/main.go"]
    
    main -->|"routes to"| assoc_cmd["assoc.CLIWorkflow()"]
    main -->|"routes to"| engine_cmd["ae.CLIWorkflow()"]
    main -->|"routes to"| enum_cmd["enum.CLIWorkflow()"]
    main -->|"routes to"| subs_cmd["subs.CLIWorkflow()"]
    main -->|"routes to"| track_cmd["track.CLIWorkflow()"]
    main -->|"routes to"| viz_cmd["viz.CLIWorkflow()"]
    
    assoc_cmd -->|"analyzes"| associations["Asset Associations"]
    engine_cmd -->|"runs"| engine_service["Amass Engine Service"]
    enum_cmd -->|"performs"| enumeration["Asset Discovery via GraphQL"]
    subs_cmd -->|"analyzes"| subdomain_data["Subdomain Analysis"]
    track_cmd -->|"tracks"| asset_changes["Asset Change Detection"]
    viz_cmd -->|"generates"| visualizations["Graph Visualizations"]
```

Sources: [cmd/amass/main.go:135-170]()

### Basic Usage Pattern

The general command structure follows this pattern:

```
amass [subcommand] [options]
```

Where `[subcommand]` is one of:
- `assoc` - Find associations between discovered assets
- `engine` - Run the Amass collection engine service
- `enum` - Interface with the engine to perform asset discovery
- `subs` - Analyze and present discovered subdomains
- `track` - Identify newly discovered assets over time
- `viz` - Generate graph visualizations of collected data

Sources: [cmd/amass/main.go:59-66]()

