The enumeration command (`enum`) is the primary interface for performing automated asset discovery using the OWASP Amass engine. It orchestrates network mapping, subdomain discovery, and infrastructure analysis by connecting to the Amass engine service and submitting enumeration targets for processing.

For information about running the engine service itself, see [Engine Command](#2.3). For analyzing enumeration results, see [Intelligence and Analysis Commands](#2.2).

