## Memory and Resource Management

The dispatcher implements memory management and resource control mechanisms to handle large-scale asset discovery operations.

### Memory Management

The dispatcher monitors heap usage and triggers garbage collection when memory pressure exceeds thresholds:

```go
// Memory monitoring (dispatcher.go:105-118)
func checkOnTheHeap() {
    var mstats runtime.MemStats
    runtime.ReadMemStats(&mstats)
    
    h := mstats.HeapAlloc
    n := mstats.NextGC
    if diff := mstats.HeapAlloc - mstats.NextGC; bToMb(diff) > 500 {
        runtime.GC()  // Force garbage collection
    }
}
```

### Queue Management

Pipeline queues are automatically refilled to maintain optimal processing throughput:

```go
// Queue refilling (dispatcher.go:124-159)
const (
    MinPipelineQueueSize = 100
    MaxPipelineQueueSize = 500
)
```

