## Purpose and Scope

The Event Processing Pipeline is the core mechanism by which OWASP Amass processes asset discovery events through a multi-stage, plugin-based architecture. This document covers how events flow from initial dispatch through prioritized handler pipelines to completion callbacks.

For information about session management and scope handling, see [Session and Scope Management](#4.2). For details about the underlying data storage, see [Data Storage and Graph Database](#4.3). For plugin development specifics, see [Plugin Development](#8.2).

