This document covers the session and scope management subsystems within the Amass engine. Sessions represent active enumeration instances with their own configuration, state, and asset discovery scope. Scope management determines which assets are considered "in-scope" for discovery and how the scope can be dynamically expanded through asset associations.

For information about the overall engine architecture, see [Engine Architecture](#4). For details about data storage and the graph database, see [Data Storage and Graph Database](#4.3).

