|-------|--------|---------|
| Creation | Constructor | Initialize plugin with default configuration |
| Registration | `Start(et.Registry)` | Register handlers and configure logging |
| Operation | Handler callbacks | Process events and assets |
| Shutdown | `Stop()` | Clean up resources and log shutdown |

**Example Plugin Implementation**

The DNS service discovery plugin demonstrates the standard plugin pattern:

```go
type dnsPlugin struct {
    name   string
    log    *slog.Logger
    source *et.Source
    txt    *txtHandler
}

func (p *dnsPlugin) Start(r et.Registry) error {
    p.log = r.Log().WithGroup("plugin").With("name", p.name)
    
    // Register TXT record handler
    if err := r.RegisterHandler(&et.Handler{
        Plugin:     p,
        Name:       p.txt.name,
        Priority:   9,
        Transforms: []string{string(oam.FQDN)},
        EventType:  oam.FQDN,
        Callback:   p.txt.check,
    }); err != nil {
        return err
    }
    
    p.log.Info("plugin started")
    return nil
}
```

