This document details the service discovery plugins in OWASP Amass, which perform HTTP probing, certificate analysis, and service fingerprinting to discover and characterize network services. These plugins complement DNS-based discovery by actively probing endpoints and analyzing service-specific indicators like TLS certificates and TXT record verification strings.

For information about API integration plugins, see [API Integration Plugins](6.2). For information about the overall plugin architecture, see [Plugin Architecture and Management](6.1).

