This page documents how Amass discovers and maps network infrastructure, including the identification of IP address blocks (netblocks) and their associated Autonomous System Numbers (ASNs). The system builds a comprehensive view of network ownership and routing relationships by correlating IP addresses with their containing network blocks and the ASNs that announce them.

For DNS-based asset discovery, see [DNS-based Asset Discovery](#5.2). For WHOIS integration beyond network mapping, see [Network Infrastructure](#7).

## Architecture Overview

