    JARM_QUERY --> PORT_EDGES
    PORT_EDGES --> TARGET_FILTER
    TARGET_FILTER --> PROBE_EXECUTION
    PROBE_EXECUTION --> HASH_GENERATION
    
    HASH_GENERATION --> EDGE_PROPERTY
    EDGE_PROPERTY --> JARM_HASH
```

The JARM implementation uses the `jarm-go` library to:
1. Generate multiple TLS probes with different cipher suites
2. Analyze server responses to each probe
3. Create a 64-character hash representing the TLS implementation
4. Store the hash as an edge property on the port relationship

Sources: [engine/plugins/jarm.go:27-160](), [engine/plugins/support/fingerprinting.go:22-81]()

## DNS-Based Service Discovery

The DNS service discovery plugin (`DNS-SD`) analyzes TXT records to identify service verification records that indicate organizational relationships:

```mermaid
