## Configuration and Scope Management

HTTP probing behavior is controlled by several configuration parameters:

| Configuration | Default | Purpose |
|--------------|---------|---------|
| `Active` | false | Enable/disable active probing |
| `Scope.Ports` | [80, 443, 8080, 8443] | Ports to probe for services |
| TTL settings | Plugin-specific | Cache duration for probe results |
| `MaxInstances` | 100 | Concurrent handler instances |

The probing system respects scope boundaries and implements rate limiting to avoid overwhelming target systems. IP address sweeping is performed on discovered addresses to identify additional services within the same network segment.

