### Code Style and Standards

Amass follows Go standard code style and uses golangci-lint to enforce it. The linting configuration specifies style rules and thresholds for various code metrics.

The project also uses CodeClimate to monitor code quality with the following thresholds:

| Metric | Threshold |
|--------|-----------|
| Argument count | 5 |
| Complex logic | 4 |
| File lines | 500 |
| Method complexity | 5 |
| Method count | 20 |
| Method lines | 100 |
| Nested control flow | 4 |
| Return statements | 10 |

Sources: [.codeclimate.yml:1-37](), [.github/workflows/lint.yml:1-31]()

## Conclusion

This guide provides the essential information needed to start developing for the OWASP Amass project. By following these guidelines, you can contribute effectively to the project while maintaining its code quality and reliability standards.

For additional questions or assistance, join the OWASP Amass Discord server mentioned in the README.

