This document provides comprehensive guidance for developing plugins within the OWASP Amass framework. It covers the plugin architecture, event-driven processing model, asset creation patterns, and practical examples for extending Amass functionality.

For information about the overall engine architecture, see [Engine Architecture](#4). For details about the existing plugin system overview, see [Plugin System](#6).

## Plugin Architecture Overview

Amass uses an event-driven plugin architecture where plugins register handlers to process specific asset types and transform them into related assets. Each plugin implements the `et.Plugin` interface and can register multiple handlers for different asset transformation workflows.

### Plugin Lifecycle

